Peru May Cut Rice Output in 2010-2011, Boost Imports, USDA Says

-- B y   W h i t n e y   M c F e r r o n
-- 
2011-03-14T19:16:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/peru-may-cut-rice-output-in-2010-2011-boost-imports-usda-says.html
Peru may produce 2.435 million
metric tons of rough rice in the year that begins April 1, down
from an estimated 2.826 million a year earlier, a unit of the  U.S. Department of Agriculture  said in a  report  posted today on
its website.  Imports may jump to 250,000 tons from 90,000 tons, the
